is an ID of a previous output.

00:06:15.690 --> 00:06:21.450
So not only is Bitcoin a series
of blocks of information--

00:06:21.450 --> 00:06:27.860
each block that has 1,000 to
2,000 individual transactions--

00:06:27.860 --> 00:06:31.760
but in a sense, there's a
separate chain that's going on.

00:06:31.760 --> 00:06:33.500
I sometimes think
of a blockchain

00:06:33.500 --> 00:06:38.700
as, yes, there's the chain
of big chunks of data,

00:06:38.700 --> 00:06:41.660
