observing that, even

00:30:57.990 --> 00:31:06.040
within the most used first
central database for blockchain

00:31:06.040 --> 00:31:10.210
called Bitcoin, they chose
to use not a blockchain,

00:31:10.210 --> 00:31:13.900
but, in essence, a more
standard database to keep

00:31:13.900 --> 00:31:17.260
the unspent transaction output.

00:31:17.260 --> 00:31:20.940
Now, in a sense, it's all part
of this blockchain solution.

00:31:20.940 --> 00:31:24.130
