00:53:34.060 --> 00:53:34.863
that Anton's--

00:53:34.863 --> 00:53:36.280
back to Anton's
question-- does it

00:53:36.280 --> 00:53:37.990
mean you have to
wait 10 minutes?

00:53:37.990 --> 00:53:40.030
The actual technical
answer to that

00:53:40.030 --> 00:53:45.880
is, no, you don't have to wait
10 minutes, unless you want

00:53:45.880 --> 00:53:50.020
final settlement,
if you want finality

00:53:50.020 --> 00:53:56.140
with no counterparty
risk, no commercial risk.

00:53:56.140 --> 00:53:58.060
Hugo is saying, well,
